"v.摇摆，犹豫 【英】 v.摇摆，犹豫(to fluctuate in opinion, allegiance, or direction) 【考】 flag : vigor / lumber : grace / waver : resolution(衰弱无精力/笨拙无 优雅/动摇无坚决)demur : qualms / waver : irresoluteness(因疑虑而反对/因犹 豫而动摇) 【例】 He wavered between accepting and refusing. v. /n. 摇摆; 犹豫 【类】flag: vigor = lumber: grace = waver: resolution衰弱不精力 = 笨拙不优雅 = 动摇不坚决demur: qualms = waver: irresoluteness因疑虑反对 = 因犹豫动摇 【记】wave 波浪，是摇摆起伏的 waver (v.)  late 13c., weyveren, ""to show indecision,"" probably related to Old English wæfre ""restless, wavering,"" from Proto-Germanic *wæbraz (cognates: Middle High German wabern ""to waver,"" Old Norse vafra ""to hover about""), a frequentative form from the root of wave (v.). Related: Wavered; wavering."
